{"key":"processedPost-19457710","value":{"id":19457710,"first":19456640,"last":19461596,"when":1390424147,"utime":"01/22/14 10:55 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Svamparn said:</strong><br />Well the problem, well not the problem but I don't want to mist it so often, that's why I want to just have it in a cabinet. So i'm looking for a good ( and cheap ) automated system.<br />Got any good ideas?</blockquote><br />This indicates you don't understand mushrooms.&nbsp; You need to figure out the life cycle of mushrooms before you try to design what isn't going to work well.<br />Mushrooms require fresh, dry, air exchange to cause evaporation from the substrate.&nbsp; This evaporation is a major pinning trigger.&nbsp; You then must mist to replace this moisture.&nbsp; If you run a cool mist or anything else and get a steady-state humidity, performance will be poor.<br />The best place to hide a grow is in plain sight.<br />RR","title":"Re: Need some advice regarding automatize"}}